# Shared OAuth credentials for Google Drive sync (Android + desktop).
#
# Use an OAuth Client ID of type "Web application" in Google Cloud Console
# for the project that hosts the app's OAuth consent screen. Required setup
# for that client:
#   - Authorized redirect URIs include http://127.0.0.1 (desktop loopback)
#   - The same Google Cloud project also has an "Android" OAuth client
#     registered with the app's package name + signing-cert SHA-1 so that
#     google_sign_in can verify the device. (No client_id/secret to thread
#     through here — google_sign_in picks it up automatically via Play.)
#
# https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
#
# Both platforms read these values via flutter_dotenv (bundled as an asset).
# Without them the Sync section is hidden in Settings. We keep the file out
# of source control even though Google's docs say the secret on installed
# apps is not confidential.
#
# Why "Web application" and not "Desktop application": Drive's `drive.file`
# scope filters file visibility per-OAuth-client. To make Android and
# desktop see the same "RSVP Reader" folder we route both through the same
# Web client_id — on Android via google_sign_in's `serverClientId`, on
# desktop via the standard loopback OAuth flow.
RSVP_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=
RSVP_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=
